    <p class="text-base w-3/4 p-text">
      Our comprehensive curriculum covers a wide spectrum of subjects, from aviation regulations and meteorology to navigation and aerodynamics. Our experienced instructors ensure that you are well equipped to succeed in the written examination. We provide targeted guidance to help you not only pass the test but also acquire a good understanding of necessary aeronautical knowledge.
    </p>
  </div>
  <!--Step 3-->
  <div class="flex flex-col items-center lg:w-1/2 p-text text-gray-300">
    <div class="p-10 "><%=image_tag "commercial-step-flying-3.webp", alt: "Pilot about to go on a cross country at Ideal Aviation", class: "rounded-lg"%></div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold pb-4 font-sans mx-5 text-center uppercase font-header text-white">Step 3. Complete Requirements</h3>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4">
      Achieving your Commercial Pilot Certificate involves fulfilling specific flight requirements, including demanding long cross country flights and other critical experiences. At Ideal Aviation, our commercial program ensures that you master advanced flight maneuvers and precise navigation techniques. With your long cross country flight, you'll demonstrate your ability to plan and execute complex missions, showcasing your aptitude for real world challenges.
    </p>
  </div>
  <!--Step 4-->
  <div class="flex flex-col items-center lg:w-1/2 p-text text-gray-300 mb-10 lg:mb-0">
    <div class="p-10"><%=image_tag "commercial-checkride-pass-airplane.webp", alt: "An Ideal Aviation student right after passing his commercial checkride", class: "rounded-lg"%></div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold pb-4 font-sans mx-5 text-center uppercase font-header text-white">Step 4. Pass the Commercial Checkride</h3>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4">
      With a focus on safety and precision, our instructors ensure that you are thoroughly ready for the check ride. As you confidently take to the skies with the examiner, you'll showcase the culmination of your training and the expertise you've gained throughout your journey with Ideal Aviation.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
<!--Eligibility Reqs-->
<section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-blue-50 to-blue-200 text-black py-20">
  <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center justify-center">
    <!--Text-->
    <div class="lg:w-1/2 flex flex-col items-center lg:items-end">
      <!--Container for text to align them-->
      <div class="lg:text-left">
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-2xl lg:text-4xl text-center pb-4">Eligibility Requirements for a Commercial Pilot Certificate</h2>
        <div class="text-base px-6 lg:pl-0 lg:pr-8">
          <p class="pb-5">
            To qualify for an FAA commercial pilot license, individuals need to meet specific criteria. This includes being at least 18 years old and possessing the ability to comprehend and communicate effectively in the English language, encompassing reading, speaking, and writing skills. 
          </p>
          <p class="my-2 pb-5 font-semibold text-2xl">
            Requirements:
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside border-b-2 border-slate-300 pb-3 pl-3">
              <li class="mb-2">Holding a current private pilot certificate</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Receiving ground training from an authorized instructor or completing a home study course for aeronautical knowledge</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Logbook Endorsements from an instructor:
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 pt-2">
                  <li class="mb-2">Obtain instructor endorsements in your logbook, allowing you to take the aeronautical knowledge test.</li>
                  <li class="mb-2">Secure logbook endorsements to participate in the practical test</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li class="mb-2">Test Requirements:
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 pt-2">
                  <li class="mb-2">Pass and complete the commercial pilot knowledge test</li>
                  <li class="mb-2">Pass and complete the commercial pilot practical test, also referred to as the checkride</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </p>
          <p class="my-2 pb-5 font-semibold text-2xl">
            Aeronautical Experience & Qualifications</p>
          <p class="my-2 pb-5 font-semibold text-l">In accordance with federal regulations, you need to have documented the specified aeronautical flight experience prerequisites to qualify for a commercial pilot license.</p>
          <p class="my-2 pb-5 font-semibold text-2xl">
            Commercial Pilot Flight Time Requirements:
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside pb-3 pl-3">
              <li class="mb-2">Accumulate a total flight time of at least 250 hours</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Attain a minimum of 100 hours as pilot-in-command (PIC)</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Complete 50 hours of cross-country flight time as PIC</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Obtain 10 hours of dedicated instrument training</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Fulfill 10 hours of flight time in Technically Advanced Aircraft (TAA)</li>
              <p class="text-xs mt-4">Reference <a class="text-blue-800 hover:underline" href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-14/chapter-I/subchapter-D/part-61/subpart-F/section-61.129">14 CFR §61.129</a> for the entire list of eligibility requirements.  Note that above listed are for fixed wing.</p>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="" id="form-section"></div>
</section>
